TY  - JOUR
T1  - Impact of Work Teams on Manufacturing Performance: A Longitudinal Field Study
AU  - Banker, Rajiv D.
AU  - Field, Joy M.
AU  - Schroeder, Roger G.
AU  - Sintia, Kingshuk K.
Y1  - 1996/08/01
PY  - 1996
DA  - 1996/08/01
N1  - doi: 10.5465/256715
DO  - 10.5465/256715
T2  - Academy of Management Journal
JF  - Academy of Management Journal
JO  - AMJ
SP  - 867
EP  - 890
VL  - 39
IS  - 4
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - We report the results of a longitudinal field study examining the impact of work teams on manufacturing performance. An electromechanical assembly plant was our research site from April 1992 through December 1993; work teams were formed on its four production lines in August 1992. Our results show that both quality and labor productivity improved over time after the formation of the teams. We offer qualitative insights into the functioning of these teams and their evolution over time, leading to workplace transformation.
AB  - We report the results of a longitudinal field study examining the impact of work teams on manufacturing performance. An electromechanical assembly plant was our research site from April 1992 through December 1993; work teams were formed on its four production lines in August 1992. Our results show that both quality and labor productivity improved over time after the formation of the teams. We offer qualitative insights into the functioning of these teams and their evolution over time, leading to workplace transformation.
SN  - 0001-4273
M3  - doi: 10.5465/256715
UR  - https://doi.org/10.5465/256715
